      "text": "Mourn the lost advantage",
      "description": "Your power came from knowing things others didn't.",
      "resultText": "You feel the loss keenly—not of the secret itself, but of the leverage it provided. You'd built strategies around that information, counted on it as an asset. Now everyone has it, and you're diminished. You become bitter about whoever exposed it, paranoid about what else might be revealed. The world feels less controllable, less predictable. You start hoarding other secrets even more jealously, determined not to lose your edge again.",
